Who says the solo diner has to make do with take-out or microwavable meals? I wanted to treat myself after a long day at work, and Blue Ribbon Brasserie rewarded me in their own small but thoughtful way; here's a tip: anyone dining by themselves receives a free dessert of choice ;o) And so it was Warm Banana Walnut Bread Pudding after a dreamy meal of fresh oysters, clams and cognac. *Pins a blue ribbon to personification of restaurant*
